@startuml Text Infringement Check Flow

title Use Case 2 - Text Infringement Check

autonumber
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 25
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ResponseMessageBelowArrow true

actor Lawyer
participant "REST API" as API
participant "Text Check Service" as TextService
database "Trademark DB" as DB
participant "Async Job Queue" as Queue
participant "External Online Search Worker" as Worker
participant "External Online Sources" as Sources
participant "Result Delivery Service" as Delivery
participant "Similarity Engine" as Similarity

Lawyer -> API: Submit protected naming + suspicious naming
API -> API: Validate request
API -> API: Orchestrate workflow
API -> API: Normalize protected naming
API -> API: Normalize suspicious naming
API -> TextService: Run text-only infringement check with canonical inputs

TextService -> DB: Find Top-200 internal candidates for suspicious naming
DB --> TextService: Candidate list

loop For each internal candidate
  TextService -> Similarity: Compare protected naming with candidate
  Similarity --> TextService: Similarity score
end

TextService -> TextService: Build Top-200 internal ranking
API -> Queue: Create async external search job
Queue --> Worker: Deliver job

Worker -> Sources: Search online external sources for suspicious naming
Sources --> Worker: External candidate set
loop For each external candidate
  Worker -> Similarity: Compare protected naming with external candidate
  Similarity --> Worker: Similarity score
end
Worker -> Worker: Build Top-200 external ranking
Worker -> Delivery: Send delayed external result set
Delivery --> API: Top-200 external results (later)
API --> Lawyer: External enrichment update

TextService --> API: Top-200 internal comparison result
API --> Lawyer: Top-200 internal results (fast) + similarity explanation

note right of TextService
Responsibility: text similarity only.
No external workflow orchestration.
end note

@enduml

